.\" pi-gen-micro - build minimal Raspberry Pi OS images
.TH PI\-GEN\-MICRO 1 "2026-03-20" "pi-gen-micro" "Raspberry Pi Tools"
.SH NAME
pi\-gen\-micro \- build minimal Raspberry Pi OS images from Debian package sources
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pi\-gen\-micro
.I configuration
.RI [ target_devices ]
.br
.B pi\-gen\-micro \-\-list\-configurations
.br
.B pi\-gen\-micro \-\-list\-packages
.br
.B pi\-gen\-micro \-h | \-\-help
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B pi\-gen\-micro
builds tiny embedded operating system images for Raspberry Pi devices using the
same package sources as Raspberry Pi OS. Images are built as initramfs-based boot
images suitable for embedded systems, device provisioning, and IoT applications.
.PP
The tool assembles a minimal root filesystem by installing Debian packages into a
build directory using
.BR fakeroot (1)
and
.BR dpkg (1),
then compresses the result into a bootable image using
.BR rpi\-make\-boot\-image .
.PP
Output is written to
.I $PWD/out_image/\fR.
It is recommended to run from a temporary directory to avoid polluting the
working directory:
.PP
.RS
.nf
pushd $(mktemp \-d)
sudo pi\-gen\-micro fastboot
.fi
.RE
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.I configuration
Name of the configuration to build. Required. Use
.B \-\-list\-configurations
to see what is available.
.TP
.I target_devices
Optional comma-separated list of target devices. Limits which device trees and
firmware files are included in the image. If omitted, files for all supported
devices are included.
.RS
.PP
Supported targets:
.BR pi3 ", " cm3 ", " pi4 ", " 400 ", " cm4 ", " pi5 ", " 500 ", " cm5 ", " 02W
.RE
.TP
.B \-h\fR, \fB\-\-help
Show usage information and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-list\-configurations
List available configurations with their descriptions and exit.
Descriptions are read from the
.I description
file in each configuration directory.
.TP
.B \-\-list\-packages
List available helper packages with their descriptions and exit.
Descriptions are read from the
.I description
field in each package's
.I nfpm.yaml
file.
.SH CONFIGURATIONS
A configuration is a directory containing files that define what goes into the
image. Built-in configurations are installed to
.IR /var/lib/pi\-gen\-micro/configurations/ .
.PP
Run
.B pi\-gen\-micro \-\-list\-configurations
to see available configurations and their descriptions.
.SS Required files
.TP
.B build.parameters
Sourced as a shell script. Sets build-time variables:
.RS
.TP
.B KERNEL_BIT_SIZE
Kernel architecture, default
.IR 64 .
.TP
.B HAS_CUSTOM_KERNEL
Set to
.I 1
to use a custom kernel. Also requires
.B CUSTOM_KERNEL_PATH
and
.BR CUSTOM_KERNEL_VERSION_STR .
.RE
.TP
.B components.parameters
Sourced as a shell script. Feature flags controlling what is installed:
.RS
.TP
.B SYSTEMD=1
Use systemd as the init system (default). Set to
.I 0
for a busybox init alternative using
.I /etc/inittab
and shell scripts. Some helper packages (e.g.\&
.BR cryptroot )
require systemd.
.TP
.B SSH=1
Install dropbear SSH server. Requires a populated
.I authorized_keys
file in the prebuilts directory.
.TP
.B UDEV=1
Install udev for dynamic device management.
.TP
.B NETWORK=1
Install networking. With systemd: systemd-networkd and systemd-resolved
(requires
.BR UDEV=1 ).
Without systemd: busybox
.BR udhcpc .
.TP
.B AUTOLOGIN=1
Enable automatic root login on console and serial.
.RE
.TP
.B packages.list
Newline-separated list of additional packages to install. Packages are
resolved from the configured APT sources, including the local helper
package repository.
.TP
.B kernel_modules.list
Newline-separated list of kernel modules to include. Module dependencies
are resolved and copied using
.BR rpi\-modcopy .
.TP
.B installer_scripts.list
An executable script run after packages are installed. Despite the
.I .list
extension, this file is
.I executed
as a shell script, not read as a list. The configuration directory is
prepended to
.BR PATH ,
so other scripts in the directory can be called by name.
.TP
.B dpkg_extra_args
dpkg
.BR path-exclude / path-include
rules to reduce image size by stripping documentation, locales, etc.
Lines starting with
.B #
are comments.
.SS Optional files
.TP
.B description
A one-line description of the configuration, shown by
.B \-\-list\-configurations
and in error messages.
.TP
.B cmdline.txt
Custom kernel command line, overriding the default from prebuilts.
.TP
.B post_creation.sh
Executable script run after the full image is assembled.
.TP
.B udebs.list
Newline-separated list of udeb packages to install as substitute packages.
.TP
.B delete.list
Newline-separated list of paths to delete from the final image.
.TP
.B generic_delete.list
Newline-separated list of filename patterns to delete from the final image,
matched by
.BR find (1)
.BR \-name .
.SH HELPER PACKAGES
.B pi\-gen\-micro
ships with a local APT repository at
.IR /var/lib/pi\-gen\-micro/internal/packages/ .
Package sources live under
.IR /var/lib/pi\-gen\-micro/helper\-packages/ ,
each containing an
.I nfpm.yaml
and the files to package.
.PP
If
.BR nfpm (1)
is installed, all helper packages are automatically rebuilt from source at the
start of each build. Otherwise, pre-built
.I .deb
files are used.
.PP
Run
.B pi\-gen\-micro \-\-list\-packages
to see available helper packages and their descriptions.
.PP
To add a new helper package, create a directory with an
.I nfpm.yaml
and add it to
.I debian/install
under
.IR /var/lib/pi\-gen\-micro/helper\-packages/ .
Reference the package name in a configuration's
.IR packages.list .
.PP
External
.I .deb
files not built from nfpm sources can be placed directly in the
.I internal/packages/
directory. After adding or removing external packages, regenerate the index:
.PP
.RS
.nf
cd /var/lib/pi\-gen\-micro/internal/packages
dpkg\-scanpackages . /dev/null | gzip \-9c > Packages.gz
.fi
.RE
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B CONFIGURATION_ROOT
Path to the configurations directory. Default:
.IR /var/lib/pi\-gen\-micro/configurations/ .
.TP
.B APT_DPKG_CFG
Path to the APT/dpkg configuration directory. Default:
.IR /var/lib/pi\-gen\-micro/internal/apt .
.TP
.B PREBUILTS_DIR
Path to the prebuilt files directory. Default:
.IR /var/lib/pi\-gen\-micro/internal/prebuilts .
.TP
.B HELPER_PACKAGES_DIR
Path to helper package sources. Default:
.IR /var/lib/pi\-gen\-micro/helper\-packages .
.SH EXAMPLES
Build the fastboot image for all devices:
.PP
.RS
.nf
pushd $(mktemp \-d)
sudo pi\-gen\-micro fastboot
.fi
.RE
.PP
Build for specific devices only:
.PP
.RS
.nf
sudo pi\-gen\-micro fastboot cm5,pi5
.fi
.RE
.PP
List what's available:
.PP
.RS
.nf
pi\-gen\-micro \-\-list\-configurations
pi\-gen\-micro \-\-list\-packages
.fi
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /var/lib/pi\-gen\-micro/configurations/
Built-in configuration directories.
.TP
.I /var/lib/pi\-gen\-micro/helper\-packages/
Source directories for helper packages (nfpm definitions).
.TP
.I /var/lib/pi\-gen\-micro/internal/packages/
Local APT repository containing helper
.I .deb
packages.
.TP
.I /var/lib/pi\-gen\-micro/internal/apt/
APT and dpkg configuration used during image builds.
.TP
.I /var/lib/pi\-gen\-micro/internal/prebuilts/
Pre-built files copied into images (config.txt, cmdline.txt, passwd, etc.).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR build\-packages (1),
.BR nfpm (1),
.BR dpkg (1),
.BR fakeroot (1),
.BR rpi\-make\-boot\-image (1)
